The paper discusses a new method for semi-supervised learning that improves classification performance on several benchmarks. The paper focuses on the use of consistency-based methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses domain adaptation, which falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes a new concept and constraint, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
